stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, React 18

@EXPORTS
middleware.ts: withAuth — NextAuth middleware protecting routes

@FUNCTIONS
middleware(_req:NextRequest) → NextResponse
  purpose: protect routes via NextAuth JWT; allow /auth, require login for rest
  side-effects: none
  called-by: Next.js middleware system

@VARS_CONSTANTS
config.matcher: string[] — routes protected by middleware (dashboard, certificate, etc.)

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: app/, components/, lib/, store/, data/, hooks/, types/, stories/, __tests__/
external: next-auth/middleware, next/server

@STANDARDS
- middleware.ts at src root for route protection
- Unprotected: /auth/*, /api/*, /chapters/*, /arena/*, /onboarding/*, static assets, home
- Protected: /dashboard/*, /certificate/*, other dynamic paths

@WARNINGS
- Matcher regex is complex — test carefully when adding new public routes
